eapli.framework.domain.time

Class TimeRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • eapli.framework.domain.range.Range<Calendar>
      • eapli.framework.domain.time.TimeRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueObject, Serializable

    public class TimeRange
extends Range<Calendar>
    A concrete range for Calendars. A time range is either a closed interval between time A and time B or a closed interval starting at time A ad infinitum since this class inherits from a generic it cannot control how Calendar objects will be persisted with JPA. see TimeInterval and DateInterval
    Author:
    Paulo Gandra Sousa
